Yeah? Well, we had a team
back with the 325th Evac last year.

01:33:01.035 --> 01:33:04.789
- And what a team that was.
- Yeah. I coached the boys myself.

01:33:05.915 --> 01:33:08.834
- He's the finest coach in the Far East.
- Yeah.

01:33:08.918 --> 01:33:11.254
We're now trying to work out
a schedule of the outfits

01:33:11.337 --> 01:33:12.964
that we're going to play this year.

01:33:13.047 --> 01:33:17.426
Of course, we, you know, throw
a little money into a pot and make bets.

01:33:17.843 --> 01:33:21.264
How much money
do you put into your pot?

01:33:21.347 --> 01:33:24.850
- $5,000, $6,000.
- $5,000!

01:33:25.393 --> 01:33:28.604
Look, you know, I don't think we're
in the sort of league that you're in.

01:33:28.688 --> 01:33:32.400
Well, I'm sure we can find a date
when we can play your team.

01:33:32.483 --> 01:33:36.612
- It can be arranged.
- Yeah. I think I'll talk this over with Henry.

01:33:36.696 --> 01:33:38.698
Thanks, boys. Thanks for the drink.

01:33:38.781 --> 01:33:41.659
- Thank you.
- What the hell you…

01:33:41.742 --> 01:33:45.079
Sir, ever since the dark days
before Pearl Harbor,

01:33:45.162 --> 01:33:46.872
I've been proud to wear this uniform.

01:33:46.956 --> 01:33:48.916
- What the hell is this?
- A helicopter.

01:33:49.000 --> 01:33:52.295
Hawkeye, that man has five times
the manpower to draw on than we do.

01:33:52.378 --> 01:33:55.506
Sure, so we get ourselves a ringer, right?

01:33:55.589 --> 01:34:00.428
We get Henry to apply, make a specific
application for a neurosurgeon.

01:34:00.511 --> 01:34:04.098
He asks for Dr. Oliver Harmon Jones.

01:34:04.181 --> 01:34:08.811
- Dr. Oliver Harmon Jones?
- He's… Who is Oliver Harmon Jones?

01:34:08.894 --> 01:34:12.398
He is better known as Spearchucker Jones.

01:34:13.524 --> 01:34:15.151
- He's a good ballplayer.
- Yes!

01:34:15.234 --> 01:34:17.695
He's a negro boy,
played with the 49ers, didn't he?

01:34:17.778 --> 01:34:18.964
- Sure.
- Yeah. Sure, I remember.

01:34:18.988 --> 01:34:20.031
He's good. He's good.

01:34:20.406 --> 01:34:22.658
Henry, if we had closer relations,

01:34:22.742 --> 01:34:25.661
we wouldn't have
this misunderstanding, right?

01:34:25.745 --> 01:34:30.124
Now, that's where a football game
would help between your outfit and mine.

01:34:30.207 --> 01:34:31.226
- A football game?
- Yeah, yeah.

01:34:31.250 --> 01:34:35.254
We put up a few bets,
$5,000 maybe, and have a little fun.

01:34:35.671 --> 01:34:39.008
Special Services in Tokyo says
it's one of the best gimmicks we've got

01:34:39.091 --> 01:34:41.677
to keep the American way of life
going here in Asia.

01:34:41.761 --> 01:34:44.096
- Betting?
- No. Football.

01:34:44.680 --> 01:34:46.349
But what about Major O'Houlihan?

01:34:46.432 --> 01:34:49.101
You mean Hot Lips? Screw her.

01:34:49.185 --> 01:34:50.579
- Gee, I don't know…
- It's a helicopter, General.

01:34:50.603 --> 01:34:52.813
I know it's a helicopter.

01:34:52.897 --> 01:34:54.899
You know what?
You guys have one problem.

01:34:54.982 --> 01:34:56.418
I just wondered about the social problem,
you know.

01:34:56.442 --> 01:35:00.446
I mean, he's the only Negro officer
in the whole camp, you know.

01:35:00.946 --> 01:35:04.658
We got a problem, then
we'll stick him in here with us, baby boy.

01:35:06.202 --> 01:35:09.455
- You're serious, ain't you? You'd do that.
- Sure, I'm serious. Yeah.

01:35:10.623 --> 01:35:13.376
It's enough for me to have to put up
with you two Yankees,

01:35:13.459 --> 01:35:15.628
but I'm, you know, that's…

01:35:18.464 --> 01:35:22.259
Because of his wife, was that why?
Or was it a religious problem?

01:35:22.343 --> 01:35:25.030
- It was a conditioning problem.
- Why do they call you Spearchucker?

01:35:25.054 --> 01:35:27.181
I used to throw the javelin.

01:35:33.813 --> 01:35:37.024
All right, men, we're not here
to sell lemonade. We're here to practice.

01:35:37.108 --> 01:35:40.027
But first I'd like to
officially welcome Spearchucker.

01:35:40.111 --> 01:35:42.297
- Is it all right to call you that?
- Call me whatever you want to.

01:35:42.321 --> 01:35:44.841
Good. Well, I just want you to know
that we're all the same here

01:35:44.865 --> 01:35:47.785
on the playing field, officers and men alike.

01:35:47.868 --> 01:35:51.580
Now, we're going to begin
with the three basic principles.

01:35:51.664 --> 01:35:54.708
Organization, discipline and teamwork.

01:35:54.792 --> 01:35:55.835
- Now…
- Pardon me.

01:35:55.918 --> 01:35:59.422
- Do you mind if we limber up first?
- That's a good idea. You organize that.

01:36:02.049 --> 01:36:06.470
Move that line, hey! Hold that line, hey!

01:36:06.554 --> 01:36:10.683
<i>All right, Seidman, keep on
pushing that… Whatever you call it.</i>

01:36:10.766 --> 01:36:14.895
<i>That's good. All right, Hot Lips,
keep their arms and limbs moving there.</i>

01:36:17.314 --> 01:36:21.402
<i>Radar, you're a coach.
You're not a corporal. You're a coach,</i>

01:36:21.485 --> 01:36:23.154
<i>so keep them going through there.</i>

01:36:23.571 --> 01:36:24.738
<i>Good, Hot Lips.</i>

01:36:25.531 --> 01:36:27.616
<i>All right, Seidman, give them five.</i>

01:36:27.700 --> 01:36:29.618
<i>All right, men, take five.</i>

01:36:29.702 --> 01:36:31.287
Spearchucker.

01:36:36.208 --> 01:36:38.210
Well, we look pretty lousy, don't we?

01:36:38.294 --> 01:36:40.313
Well, for college players
that have been out of training

01:36:40.337 --> 01:36:42.441
for seven or eight years,
yeah, you look pretty lousy.

01:36:42.465 --> 01:36:44.633
Listen, I got an idea
how we can make some money.

01:36:44.717 --> 01:36:46.278
We leave him out
of the first half of the game.

01:36:46.302 --> 01:36:49.805
We bet half our money.
They roll up some points, okay?

01:36:49.889 --> 01:36:52.475
Second half of the game, we stick him in.
We get odds from them.

01:36:52.558 --> 01:36:54.768
We bet the other half of the money.
We clean up.

01:36:54.852 --> 01:36:57.646
- That's very good thinking, Captain.
- Yeah. It sounds good to me.

01:36:57.730 --> 01:37:01.150
And I had another idea.
I think we should have some plays.

01:37:01.233 --> 01:37:04.069
You know, usually in football,
you have some organized plays.

01:37:04.153 --> 01:37:07.573
- Well, if you don't mind, I took the liberty.
- You have.

01:37:07.656 --> 01:37:10.326
- I drew up about seven or eight plays.
- These are good.

01:37:10.409 --> 01:37:12.249
I think that's about all
this bunch can handle.

01:37:12.328 --> 01:37:16.081
Very good. Yes. Very, very good.

01:37:17.625 --> 01:37:18.792
What are these little arrows?

01:37:56.622 --> 01:37:58.415
- Right into his hands.
- Right on!

01:38:15.266 --> 01:38:18.060
- Well, it's only six points.
- Six points.

01:38:25.818 --> 01:38:27.418
- Well, it's only one point.
- One point!

01:38:27.486 --> 01:38:29.965
Who's that number one? That man
runs like a rabbit. We can't stop him.

01:38:29.989 --> 01:38:32.050
Yeah. I remember him from the pros.
They call him Super Bug.

01:38:32.074 --> 01:38:33.635
He had one year with the Rams
before the army got him.

01:38:33.659 --> 01:38:36.763
- We can't do anything with him in there.
- Hey, listen. You got to come in now.

01:38:36.787 --> 01:38:37.931
- We can't wait till the second half.
- No, no.

01:38:37.955 --> 01:38:39.140
We got to stick to our strategy,

01:38:39.164 --> 01:38:41.643
but the first thing you guys have to do
is get him out of the ballgame.

01:38:41.667 --> 01:38:43.419
Hey, Davidson! Here.

01:38:44.044 --> 01:38:48.132
Let's ease up just a little bit.
We don't want the score too lopsided.

01:38:54.680 --> 01:38:56.181
He caught it!

01:38:58.684 --> 01:39:00.603
- Get him!
- Get him!

01:39:05.858 --> 01:39:07.192
- Go get him!
- Go get him!

01:39:09.695 --> 01:39:10.821
Who's he giving it to?

01:39:10.904 --> 01:39:14.742
- Isn't that Corporal Judson with the ball?
- Judson's a lineman. Judson can't run!

01:39:14.825 --> 01:39:16.577
He's loose. He's loose.

01:39:21.081 --> 01:39:24.293
For crying out loud, Judson,
what're you doing?

01:39:24.376 --> 01:39:26.855
- Duke, you threw me that damn ball.
- Come on, let's get in a huddle.

01:39:26.879 --> 01:39:28.631
What the hell?
You had the whole field open!

01:39:28.714 --> 01:39:30.299
Why'd you go and fall down for?

01:39:30.382 --> 01:39:32.217
I'm no goddamn runner. I'm a lineman.

01:39:35.054 --> 01:39:37.431
We're going to really clean up today.

01:39:37.514 --> 01:39:39.183
Hut one, hut two!

01:39:49.360 --> 01:39:52.696
- It's only two points.
- Two points.

01:39:52.780 --> 01:39:55.157
What the hell you think you are,
a cannon?

01:39:55.240 --> 01:39:56.533
What kind of a snap was that?

01:39:56.617 --> 01:39:59.620
We got a lot of money on this game.
This is embarrassing, man.

01:39:59.703 --> 01:40:02.915
- Oh, go, we want some dough!
- Oh, go, we want some dough!

01:40:08.379 --> 01:40:10.214
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

01:40:12.049 --> 01:40:14.677
- What happens now?
- We get a free kick.

01:40:14.760 --> 01:40:17.179
A free kick! Girls!

01:40:17.262 --> 01:40:20.432
- Hit that ball! Kick that ball!
- Hit that ball! Kick that ball!

01:40:46.792 --> 01:40:49.920
- Another six points.
- Another six points.

01:40:53.549 --> 01:40:56.135
Look, look, he's hurt.

01:40:56.218 --> 01:40:58.220
He's leaving the game!

01:40:58.303 --> 01:41:02.057
He's hurt! He's hurt!
He's leaving the game! He's hurt!

01:41:02.141 --> 01:41:05.894
He's hurt! He's hurt!
He's leaving the game! He's hurt!

01:41:05.978 --> 01:41:08.313
What the hell's the matter with you?
Smith!

01:41:08.397 --> 01:41:12.735
- Goddamn bastards pulled something.
- Hey, Coach, did I break my 9 in 400?

01:41:12.818 --> 01:41:15.696
400! This is not a track meet.
This is a football game.

01:41:15.779 --> 01:41:17.906
What the hell do you think I pay you for?

01:41:17.990 --> 01:41:20.242
Get him up. Walk him around.
Do something.

01:41:20.325 --> 01:41:25.164
- I think I'll run the 440.
- 440! This is a football game, God damn it!

01:41:32.045 --> 01:41:34.673
All right, you guys,
get in there and kill them!

01:41:46.977 --> 01:41:49.097
All right, bub, your fucking head
is coming right off.

01:41:59.823 --> 01:42:02.201
- I'm ready, Coach. Ready, Coach.
- Ready for what?

01:42:02.284 --> 01:42:06.121
- I'm in the broad jump, Coach.
- Get him back on the bench. Broad jump!

01:42:06.205 --> 01:42:09.458
- Still 16-0.
- 16-0.

01:42:09.541 --> 01:42:12.920
Well, that's not bad. 16-0 in the first half.

01:42:13.003 --> 01:42:15.398
I guess I have to give them
the old Knute Rockne at half-time.

01:42:15.422 --> 01:42:17.466
- About time for the gun.
- Right.

01:42:22.054 --> 01:42:23.948
Hurts like a mother,
but how are we gonna score…

01:42:23.972 --> 01:42:28.268
Men, ever since the dark days
before Pearl Harbor,

01:42:28.352 --> 01:42:30.622
- I've been proud to wear this uniform.
- Boone, you got a towel?

01:42:30.646 --> 01:42:33.124
- Henry, have you pressed the bets yet?
- Today we are wearing…

01:42:33.148 --> 01:42:34.828
Henry, have you pressed
the bets yet, babe?

01:42:34.900 --> 01:42:36.900
- The bets, the bets!
- Henry, press the bets, man.

01:42:37.069 --> 01:42:38.612
Finish, finish the half-time speech.

01:42:39.613 --> 01:42:42.783
Hit them with a mortar!
Kick them off the hill!

01:42:42.866 --> 01:42:46.226
- Mash them! Smash them! Kill! Kill! Kill!
- Mash them! Smash them! Kill! Kill! Kill!

01:42:46.286 --> 01:42:50.082
Hot Lips! There's a time
and a place for everything, damn it!

01:42:51.208 --> 01:42:53.836
- Right. Bo-bo.
- Bo! Bo!

01:42:53.919 --> 01:42:56.296
Come on, Smitty. Come on, boy.

01:42:58.549 --> 01:43:00.235
- What's the matter with him?
- What's the matter with him?

01:43:00.259 --> 01:43:03.262
Hell, you ought to know.
You guys pulled something out there.

01:43:03.345 --> 01:43:05.185
Well, I guess you don't
want to double the bet.

01:43:05.264 --> 01:43:06.807
The hell I don't.

01:43:06.890 --> 01:43:09.560
We were beating you without him,
and we'll go on beating you.

01:43:09.643 --> 01:43:11.246
Are you prepared
to back that up with odds?

01:43:11.270 --> 01:43:14.064
Damn right. Three to one. Double the bet.

01:43:27.452 --> 01:43:29.371
Who's that 24? Who is he?

01:43:32.291 --> 01:43:34.042
Stop him! Stop him!

01:43:35.127 --> 01:43:39.798
Stop him! Stop him! Who is that guy?
He wasn't in the game in the first half.

01:43:39.882 --> 01:43:41.300
Stop him!

01:43:51.393 --> 01:43:53.896
- That's Spearchucker Jones.
- Spearchucker who?

01:43:53.979 --> 01:43:56.064
He played with San Francisco
before he got drafted.

01:43:56.148 --> 01:43:58.108
Boy, he's going to be tough to stop, too.

01:43:58.817 --> 01:44:00.903
Henry, you brought in a ringer, did you?

01:44:00.986 --> 01:44:05.949
- Radar, what's the general trying to say?
- Didn't bring him in the first half, did you?

01:44:06.033 --> 01:44:10.287
He's just been informed
as to the identity of our Spearchucker.

01:44:10.370 --> 01:44:12.289
His ringer's spotted our ringer.

01:44:12.372 --> 01:44:15.167
How do you like them apples, Charlie?

01:44:15.250 --> 01:44:19.504
- You can't trust anybody.
- Now watch him make the extra point.

01:44:25.677 --> 01:44:26.970
Isn't that illegal?

01:45:12.391 --> 01:45:16.979
What kind of team is it?
They're falling all around like dead flies!

01:45:26.029 --> 01:45:30.701
- Look! A red flag! We've got a red flag!
- Hot Lips!

01:45:32.911 --> 01:45:34.431
It's a penalty, you blithering idiots.

01:45:42.129 --> 01:45:46.341
Judson, get off of him.
You'll be thrown out of the game.

01:45:46.425 --> 01:45:48.468
Judson, kill him!

01:45:55.350 --> 01:45:59.187
What's wrong with you, huh?
We're here to play football, not fight!

01:46:02.065 --> 01:46:05.819
- Bastard 88 called me a coon.
- Called you a what?

01:46:07.112 --> 01:46:08.363
Coon.

01:46:09.364 --> 01:46:12.659
Okay, that's an old pro trick
to get you thrown out of the ballgame.

01:46:13.243 --> 01:46:15.203
Why don't you do the same thing to him?

01:46:15.287 --> 01:46:16.872
What, call him a coon?

01:46:16.955 --> 01:46:19.166
No, no, the boys in camp
used to talk about his sister.

01:46:19.249 --> 01:46:21.334
Her name was Gladys. Use it!

01:46:23.170 --> 01:46:25.380
- Yeah.
- All right, all right.

01:46:43.982 --> 01:46:46.651
What the hell are you doing,
for God's sake?

01:46:47.402 --> 01:46:48.820
What's the matter here?

01:46:49.696 --> 01:46:51.114
They're taking him out.

01:46:58.705 --> 01:47:03.668
- 69 is divine! 69 is divine!
- 69 is divine! 69 is divine!

01:47:03.752 --> 01:47:08.465
There you go, Charlie.
Another side of beef for your butcher shop.

01:47:08.548 --> 01:47:12.385
Let's get the ball and really go!
Hey, hey! Ho, ho!

01:47:12.469 --> 01:47:15.597
- Who's the brunette? She a new one?
- Yeah, I just had her shipped in.

01:47:15.680 --> 01:47:18.850
Yeah. Not bad.
Kill them! Kill them, God damn it!

01:47:23.438 --> 01:47:25.774
My God! They've shot him!

01:47:25.857 --> 01:47:29.653
Hot Lips, you incredible nincompoop.
It's the end of the quarter.

01:47:29.736 --> 01:47:33.406
What did I make you a major for?
For a team like that?

01:47:33.490 --> 01:47:34.717
I did the best I could, Charlie.

01:47:34.741 --> 01:47:36.260
I didn't know
they were going to bring in a ringer.

01:47:36.284 --> 01:47:37.637
I ought to put you in there
and let them kill you,

01:47:37.661 --> 01:47:38.703
is what I ought to do.

01:47:38.787 --> 01:47:40.389
What about my knee, Charlie?
Remember my knee.

01:47:40.413 --> 01:47:44.084
You better get on your goddamn knee
and start praying. Trick knee, my ass.

01:48:16.366 --> 01:48:17.826
My God!

01:48:28.253 --> 01:48:29.921
- How's that?
- Did you see that?

01:48:30.005 --> 01:48:33.216
Get the hell back there. Get back there.

01:48:57.032 --> 01:49:00.493
Well, looks like we may make it.
Seconds to go.

01:49:00.577 --> 01:49:02.746
Okay, fellas,
we don't have very much time left.

01:49:02.829 --> 01:49:04.015
Now, I just checked with the ref.

01:49:04.039 --> 01:49:06.875
I got a special play I want to run with,
a center eligible play.

01:49:06.958 --> 01:49:10.378
We line up with everybody to the right
of the center except Hawkeye,

01:49:10.462 --> 01:49:13.381
who drops back one yard
just before the snap of the ball.

01:49:13.465 --> 01:49:14.942
Now, that makes you the semi-eligible,

01:49:14.966 --> 01:49:18.553
but all you have to do is take the ball
right back from Trapper between your legs

01:49:18.637 --> 01:49:23.558
and hide it under your belly
and walk toward their goal. All right?

01:49:23.642 --> 01:49:24.768
Trapper.

01:49:26.186 --> 01:49:27.187
We got it.

01:49:27.312 --> 01:49:30.899
All right. This is only one time. $5,000.

01:49:30.982 --> 01:49:32.734
- Worth a try.
- It'd be a miracle.

01:49:32.817 --> 01:49:33.818
I'm short one.

01:49:33.902 --> 01:49:35.671
- What do you say? What do you say?
- Let's do it now!

01:49:35.695 --> 01:49:36.821
Ready, Hawk?

01:49:36.905 --> 01:49:37.906
Ready!

01:49:39.616 --> 01:49:40.659
Set!

01:49:53.713 --> 01:49:56.424
- What are you doing? Get back!
- I got the ball!

01:49:56.508 --> 01:49:57.717
Run with it!

01:51:28.141 --> 01:51:30.185
- Two dollars.
- Two dollars.

01:51:34.105 --> 01:51:35.607
Four dollars.

01:51:36.608 --> 01:51:38.818
Out. I fold.

01:51:39.069 --> 01:51:41.696
Raise you two more. You raise his two?

01:51:43.531 --> 01:51:44.949
Raise you another two.

01:51:46.034 --> 01:51:49.037
- I have an Oklahoma.
- Oh, God!

01:51:52.457 --> 01:51:54.268
- What is that?
- Oklahoma. It's a pair of eights,

01:51:54.292 --> 01:51:56.628
- a ten of spades, a deuce, and a five.
- You win!

01:51:56.711 --> 01:51:58.546
What are you talking about?
What do you have?

01:51:58.630 --> 01:51:59.798
<i>Tokyo.</i>

01:52:00.298 --> 01:52:03.635
<i>The United States Armed Forces
Radio is on the air.</i>

01:52:37.168 --> 01:52:39.170
Duke? You busy?

01:52:41.256 --> 01:52:45.009
- What is it?
- Henry's got our orders. We can go home.

01:52:57.564 --> 01:52:58.731
Right now?

01:52:59.274 --> 01:53:01.693
Any time. Whenever we want.

01:53:01.776 --> 01:53:04.362
Do you mind
if we get out of this guy's brain first?

01:53:09.200 --> 01:53:12.829
Can't you sew this thing up?
You got that vessel under control.

01:53:14.706 --> 01:53:15.707
Haven't you?

01:53:16.708 --> 01:53:19.669
I want to make sure the oozing
is completely checked before I close up.

01:53:19.752 --> 01:53:21.212
Damn perfectionist.

01:53:23.465 --> 01:53:25.049
Yeah, well, I'm…

01:53:27.135 --> 01:53:28.136
I'll see you.

01:53:32.724 --> 01:53:33.808
Five goddamn months,

01:53:33.892 --> 01:53:37.562
and they don't even give a guy
time off for good behavior.

01:53:37.645 --> 01:53:40.607
Hey, hey, man, see you around.

01:53:40.690 --> 01:53:42.192
It's possible.

01:53:43.026 --> 01:53:44.652
Take care of the squirrels.

01:53:51.034 --> 01:53:52.660
So long, Pup-Pup.

01:53:55.747 --> 01:53:57.027
Will you go, for Christ's sakes?

01:53:57.081 --> 01:54:00.001
Will you go before they change their mind?
Get out of here!

01:54:00.084 --> 01:54:02.962
"O Lord God,
listen favorably to our prayers

01:54:03.046 --> 01:54:06.132
"and with your right hand bless this jeep.

01:54:06.216 --> 01:54:08.593
"Send your holy angels
so that all who ride in it

01:54:08.676 --> 01:54:11.262
"may be delivered and guarded
from every danger.

01:54:11.346 --> 01:54:12.972
"And as you granted faith and grace

01:54:13.056 --> 01:54:15.808
"by your deacon Philip
to the man from Ethiopia,

01:54:15.892 --> 01:54:19.145
"who was sitting in his chariot
and reading holy scripture,

01:54:19.229 --> 01:54:21.814
"show the way of salvation
to your servants,

01:54:21.898 --> 01:54:25.527
"so that helped by your grace
and always intent on doing good works,

01:54:25.610 --> 01:54:29.531
"they may, after all the trials
of their pilgrimage and life on earth,

01:54:29.614 --> 01:54:33.952
"attain to everlasting joys
through Christ, our Lord. Amen."

01:54:35.537 --> 01:54:37.598
Captain Pierce,
your driver will be here in just a minute.

01:54:37.622 --> 01:54:39.749
- Yes, sir.
- Have a good trip, sir.

01:54:39.832 --> 01:54:41.251
Now, let's go, driver.

01:54:43.211 --> 01:54:47.090
<i>Attention.
Tonight's movie has been</i> MASH.

01:54:47.173 --> 01:54:49.759
<i>Follow the zany antics
of our combat surgeons</i>

01:54:49.842 --> 01:54:54.347
<i>as they cut and stitch their way
along the frontlines.</i>

01:54:54.430 --> 01:54:56.474
<i>Operating as bombs…</i>

01:54:57.392 --> 01:55:00.770
<i>Operating as bombs and bullets
burst around them,</i>

01:55:00.853 --> 01:55:04.816
<i>snatching laughs and love
between amputations and penicillin.</i>

01:55:04.899 --> 01:55:06.901
Did Hawkeye steal that jeep?

01:55:08.236 --> 01:55:11.281
- No, sir. That's the one he came in.
- Very good. Come along, my dear.

01:55:11.864 --> 01:55:15.368
<i>Follow Hawkeye, Trapper, Duke, Dago Red,</i>

01:55:15.451 --> 01:55:20.081
<i>Painless, Radar, Hot Lips,
Dish and Staff Sergeant Vollmer</i>

01:55:20.164 --> 01:55:22.417
<i>as they put our boys back together again.</i>

01:55:22.500 --> 01:55:25.253
<i>Starring Donald Sutherland, Elliott Gould,</i>

01:55:25.336 --> 01:55:28.339
<i>Tom Skerritt, Sally Kellerman,
Robert Duvall,</i>

01:55:28.423 --> 01:55:32.468
<i>Jo Ann Pflug, Rene Auberjonois,
Roger Bowen, Gary Burghoff, David Arkin,</i>

01:55:32.552 --> 01:55:34.637
<i>John Schuck, Fred Williamson,
Indus Arthur,</i>

01:55:34.721 --> 01:55:36.973
<i>Tim Brown, Corey Fischer, Bud Cort,</i>

01:55:37.056 --> 01:55:41.227
<i>Carl Gottlieb, Dawne Damon, Tamara
Horrocks, Ken Prymus, Danny Goldman,</i>

01:55:41.311 --> 01:55:44.480
<i>Kim Atwood, Michael Murphy,
G. Wood, Rick Neilan and Bobby Troup.</i>

01:55:44.564 --> 01:55:47.191
- Goddamn army.
